  <context>
    <background>
      r1's `priority-order.md` left 3 sibling-owner sign-off slots as TBD because outreach couldn't complete within r1's test-only scope. r2's FR-06 closes those slots. In parallel, RB-T028-02 (Insights Layer 2 outcome-extraction fixture drift) is on HOLD pending `ai-spaarke-insights-engine-r1` owner sign-off — r2's FR-05 resolves the HOLD with one of three outcomes within a 1-week response window. If the owner does not respond, the entry is archived as `archived-pending-sibling-engagement` (per FR-05). The 1-week timeout protects the 2026-08-31 deadline; this task initiates the clock.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="000" status="must-complete-first">Baseline must be captured before outreach so owner queries reference the documented r2 starting state</dependency>
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <relevant-files>
    <file>projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/decisions/owner-responses/action-engine.md</file>
    <file>projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/decisions/owner-responses/insights.md</file>
