  </relevant-files>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/priority-order.md` to identify the 3 TBD sibling-owner sign-off slots (Action Engine, Insights, Communications); capture each slot's surrounding context (which BFF surface areas overlap).</step>
    <step order="2">For each sibling, draft an outreach message stub in `decisions/owner-responses/{action-engine,insights,communications}.md` containing: project context; specific overlap (e.g., "Communications owns ArchivalFlow tests that r1 task 011 repaired"); sign-off question; 1-week response deadline.</step>
    <step order="3">For Insights specifically, draft a separate query about RB-T028-02 (Layer 2 outcome-extraction fixture drift) — 3 tests in `Services.Ai.Insights.Layer2.Layer2OutcomeExtractionTests` — asking whether they own the bug (FR-05 path-a) or whether r2 should take it (path-b). Include 1-week timeout clause for path-c (archived).</step>
    <step order="4">Dispatch the outreach (via the channel the owner uses — capture the dispatch event in each response file with timestamp). For this task's purposes, the outreach action is documented (not actually sent through external mail). The owner will run the actual dispatch.</step>
    <step order="5">Set a 1-week reminder; capture the response window end date in `decisions/D-07-insights-layer2-resolution-path.md` (draft state — final decision is gated on response).</step>
    <step order="6">As responses come in (could be days after dispatch): update each owner-response file with the response content + date; for Insights, update D-07 to reflect the chosen path (a/b/c).</step>
    <step order="7">After the 1-week window closes (or earlier if all responses received): update `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/priority-order.md` with owner names + sign-off dates (or "no in-flight overlap" / "owner unresponsive — archived per FR-05" annotations).</step>
    <step order="8">Update `projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md` — mark 002 as ✅; note any branching: if FR-05 path-b chosen, task 012 takes the production fix; if path-a or path-c, task 012 is scoped accordingly.</step>
    <step order="9">Update `projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/current-task.md` with completion note.</step>
    <step order="10">Commit message: "docs(projects/r2): sibling-owner outreach + Insights HOLD resolution (FR-05, FR-06)" — references both FRs.</step>
  </steps>

